"Deletes any existing lore chunks for the save, then embeds each entry "
"tagged ``chunk_type=\"lore\"`` and ``turn_id=0`` (timeless → survives any"
" rewind) with its ``entry_id`` in metadata, so a retrieval hit maps back "
"to the structured row for link expansion. Call once per session (and "
"after a hot reload) to keep lore embeddings in sync with the definition. "
"No-op when the embedding runtime is unavailable."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.memory.VectorMemory.sync_lore:10 of
msgid "The save whose lore embeddings are (re)built."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.memory.VectorMemory.sync_lore:11 of
msgid "Lore rows, each a dict with ``entry_id`` and ``text``."
msgstr ""

